name: ibis-framework
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "0.10.0" %}

package:
  name: ibis-framework
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: ibis-framework-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/i/ibis-framework/ibis-framework-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  md5: 63543265b33269b129e1f9ddaaab809e

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - pytest
    - numpy >=1.9.0
    - pandas >=0.19.0
    - impyla >=0.14.0
    - python-hdfs >=2.0.0
    - sqlalchemy >=1.0.0
    - six
    - mock  # [py<35]

  run:
    - python
    - pytest
    - numpy >=1.9.0
    - pandas >=0.19.0
    - impyla >=0.14.0
    - python-hdfs >=2.0.0
    - sqlalchemy >=1.0.0
    - six
    - toolz
    - mock  # [py<35]

test:
  imports:
    - ibis
    - ibis.expr
    - ibis.expr.tests
    - ibis.hive
    - ibis.hive.tests
    - ibis.impala
    - ibis.impala.tests
    - ibis.spark
    - ibis.spark.tests
    - ibis.sql
    - ibis.sql.presto
    - ibis.sql.presto.tests
    - ibis.sql.redshift
    - ibis.sql.redshift.tests
    - ibis.sql.sqlite
    - ibis.sql.sqlite.tests
    - ibis.sql.tests
    - ibis.sql.vertica
    - ibis.sql.vertica.tests
    - ibis.tests

about:
  license: Apache 2.0
  home: http://www.ibis-project.org
  summary: 'Productivity-centric Python Big Data Framework'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - cpcloud
    - mariusvniekerk
    - wesm
